    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>
      The Hubble Census of Nearby Satellites is an international collaboration that seeks to deepen our understanding of low-mass galaxies. The group intends to use Hubble data to explore all satellite galaxies orbiting Milky Way-like galaxies within 10 megaparsecs. The survey aims to eliminate any potential bias that could be hidden within the Local Group. 
